      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's just... social services won't change the fact that they're exhausted. i see it in my daughter's eyes every time i ask for help with the stairs or the meds. they're giving up their own lives just to keep me going. i've always tried to be a provider, to be the one people could rely on, and now i'm just the person everyone has to manage. it feels so wrong to keep taking from them when i have nothing left to give.",
